  "name": "Cleansing Flame",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/spells/explosion-orange-2.jpg",
  "sort": 0,
  "flags": {},
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 9th level, twice per day, you can use fire to restore the health of yourself or your allies. As a standard action, you can wreathe your hand in a halo of flame and touch yourself or another creature. The touch heals 2d8 + your character level points of damage. You can also remove one of the following conditions affecting the target: 1d6 points of <em>ability damage</em>, <em>blinded</em>, <em>confused</em>, <em>dazzled</em>, <em>deafened</em>, diseased, <em>exhausted</em>, <em>fatigued</em>, <em>nauseated</em>, poisoned, or <em>sickened</em>. At 20th level, you can use this ability three times per day.</p>"
